Aim: Initial settings - Adding users, Network settings, Configure services and Listing services.

Add a user Command follows:-

Step 1 : Add a new user using 
Command :- sudo adduser <username>

Step 2 : Create a password for the user
Command :- $passwd username

Step 3 : terminal ask you for type password two time. After that it creates new user.
Step 4 : Password updated successfully.

Network Setting :- 
Step 5 : iP Address 
Command :- sudo ifconfig -a or  ifconfig

Step 6 : To enable service
Command :- sudo systemctl enable <service_name>

Step 7: To start service
Command :- sudo systemctl start <service_name>

Step 8 : To stop service
Command :- sudo systemctl stop <service_name>

Step 09 : sudo setting:- 
Command :- sudo apt install package-name

Step 10 : Display the list of services which are running:-  
Command:- sudo systemctl list-units --type=service --state=running
